The Watercone
Uploaded on Nov 12, 2007 The Watercone® is a solar powered water desalinator that takes salt or brackish water and generates freshwater. It is simple to use, lightweight and mobile. The technology is simple in design and use and is described by easy to understand pictograms. With max. 1,6 liters a day the Watercone® is an ideal device to cover a childs daily need of freshwater. UNICEF: &ldquo;every day 5000 children die as a result of diarrhea coused by drinking unsafe water&rdquo;
